## Distilled 2026-04-05

## Distilled 2026-04-06 — TG Community Catalog (2,129 workflows)

### AI Agent Architecture (dominant pattern — 65% of all workflows)

- [PATTERN] **Standard AI Agent chain**: trigger → AI:agent node + AI:lmChat{Model} + AI:outputParserStructured → action node. Used in 1,395/2,129 workflows. The agent node is the universal orchestrator. <!-- decay:2026-04-06 tier:cold rel:0.58 -->
- [PATTERN] **Model selection**: OpenAI (994 uses), Google Gemini (447), Groq (for speed), OpenRouter (model routing), DeepSeek (budget). Use OpenRouter for fallback across providers. <!-- decay:2026-04-06 tier:cold rel:0.58 -->
- [PATTERN] **Memory patterns**: AI:memoryBufferWindow (355 uses) is the default for chat-based agents. For persistent memory: memoryPostgresChat or memoryRedisChat. Buffer window = simple, Postgres = durable. <!-- decay:2026-04-06 tier:cold rel:0.58 -->
- [PATTERN] **Structured output**: AI:outputParserStructured (658 uses) — always parse LLM output to JSON schema. Prevents downstream node failures from unstructured text. <!-- decay:2026-04-06 tier:cold rel:0.58 -->

### Top Trigger Patterns

- [PATTERN] **scheduleTrigger → AI → HTTP/Sheets** (298 workflows): The "content machine" pattern. Cron fires → AI generates/processes → stores in Google Sheets or sends via HTTP. Used for: blog automation, newsletter generation, social media scheduling, market monitoring. <!-- decay:2026-04-06 tier:cold rel:0.58 -->
- [PATTERN] **telegramTrigger → AI agent + memory → telegram response** (182 workflows): The "smart bot" pattern. User sends message → agent with buffer memory processes → responds in same chat. Add tools (Google Calendar, Gmail, HTTP) for multi-capability bots. <!-- decay:2026-04-06 tier:cold rel:0.58 -->
- [PATTERN] **webhook → AI agent → respondToWebhook** (175 workflows): The "API endpoint" pattern. External service calls n8n → AI processes request → returns structured response. Used for: CRM integration, chatbot backends, form processing. <!-- decay:2026-04-06 tier:cold rel:0.58 -->
- [PATTERN] **formTrigger → AI → action** (151 workflows): The "smart form" pattern. User fills n8n form → AI enriches/classifies input → creates document, sends email, or updates CRM. Low-code lead generation. <!-- decay:2026-04-06 tier:cold rel:0.58 -->
- [PATTERN] **chatTrigger → AI agent** (33 workflows): The "embedded chat" pattern. n8n's built-in chat widget as frontend. Quick prototyping without Telegram/web integration. <!-- decay:2026-04-06 tier:cold rel:0.58 -->

### Integration Patterns

- [PATTERN] **Google Sheets as lightweight DB**: 1,648 uses across workflows. Primary data store for: lead tracking, content calendars, monitoring logs. Cheaper and simpler than Postgres for small-scale automation. <!-- decay:2026-04-06 tier:cold rel:0.58 -->
- [PATTERN] **HTTP Request as universal connector**: 3,524 uses. For any API without a native n8n node — Firecrawl, HeyGen, Dumpling AI, custom webhooks. Always pair with error handling (IF node check status code). <!-- decay:2026-04-06 tier:cold rel:0.58 -->
- [PATTERN] **Code node for transformations**: 3,070 uses. When Set/IF nodes are insufficient — complex data mapping, regex extraction, API response parsing. JS only (no Python). <!-- decay:2026-04-06 tier:cold rel:0.58 -->

### Extracted from claudeclaw-features triage (2026-04-12)

- [PATTERN] **Reels сценарии из топ-видео**: Apify Instagram Scraper → Whisper транскрипция → Claude анализ паттернов → 7 сценариев (Hook → Problem → Solution → How to) → Google Sheets. Формат: `scheduleTrigger → Apify → OpenAI → Claude → Sheets`. <!-- decay:2026-04-06 tier:cold rel:0.58 -->
- [PATTERN] **RSS + AI → WordPress черновики**: RSS-ленты → AI рерайт/адаптация → WordPress draft post. Автоматизация блога без ручного контента. Подходит для studiokook.ee новости/тренды. <!-- decay:2026-04-06 tier:cold rel:0.58 -->
- [PATTERN] **Форма бронирования + Google Calendar**: n8n form → проверка свободных слотов в Calendar → создание события → подтверждение email через Gmail. Применимо для Studiokook (бронирование консультаций). <!-- decay:2026-04-06 tier:cold rel:0.58 -->
- [PATTERN] **Глобальное key-value хранилище**: n8n Data Tables как персистентное хранилище переменных между workflow runs. Замена для globals/env: состояние между запусками, кеш API-ответов, счётчики. <!-- decay:2026-04-06 tier:cold rel:0.58 -->
- [PATTERN] **Многоязычный перевод DeepL + GPT-4o-mini**: DeepL для точного перевода → GPT для адаптации тона/контекста → Google Sheets лог. Для 4-язычного Studiokook (ET/RU/EN/FI). <!-- decay:2026-04-06 tier:cold rel:0.58 -->
- [PATTERN] **Авто-загрузка видео на YouTube с SEO**: генерация title/description/tags через AI → YouTube API upload → SEO-оптимизация метаданных. OAuth2 + n8n HTTP Request. <!-- decay:2026-04-06 tier:cold rel:0.58 -->
- [PATTERN] **Async API polling (kie.ai / image gen)**: formTrigger → GPT-4 (web search, формирует промпт) → HTTP Request (POST /jobs/createTask) → Loop: Wait 15s → GET /jobs/recordInfo → IF status=success → Download + Email; IF попытки>20 → Error Email. Шаблон применим ко всем async генераторам с polling API. <!-- decay:2026-04-06 tier:cold rel:0.58 -->

### Self-Improving / RAG Patterns

- [PATTERN] **Vector store + document loader + embeddings → retrieval agent**: Supabase (pgvector), Pinecone, Qdrant, Weaviate as vector stores. Pattern: ingest docs → chunk → embed → store. Query: user input → embed → similarity search → inject context → LLM responds. <!-- decay:2026-04-06 tier:cold rel:0.58 -->
- [PATTERN] **Human-in-the-loop knowledge expansion**: webhook receives question → agent searches KB → if not found → escalate to human → LLM generalizes answer → write back to KB. Each escalation permanently expands coverage. (File: `Самосовершенствующаяся_поддержка_ИИ_электронной_почты.json`) <!-- decay:2026-04-06 tier:cold rel:0.58 -->
- [PATTERN] **Positive/negative feedback stores**: Two separate vector collections — successful responses and failed responses. Agent searches both before answering, avoids repeating mistakes. (File: `Создайте_чат_бота_с_обратной_связью.json`) <!-- decay:2026-04-06 tier:cold rel:0.58 -->

### Content Pipeline Patterns

- [PATTERN] **Full content machine**: Schedule → RSS/scrape → AI summarize → Google Sheets (content calendar) → AI generate post → publish to WordPress/social. Example: 81-node blog automation workflow. <!-- decay:2026-04-06 tier:cold rel:0.58 -->
- [PATTERN] **Video generation pipeline**: Schedule → AI script generation → HeyGen/Seedance API for avatar video → upload to TikTok/YouTube/Instagram. Multiple 30-40 node workflows for this pattern. <!-- decay:2026-04-06 tier:cold rel:0.58 -->
- [PATTERN] **Newsletter from YouTube**: YouTube transcript → AI extract key points → format as newsletter draft → Gmail send. 8-node minimal workflow. <!-- decay:2026-04-06 tier:cold rel:0.58 -->

### n8n Template Import — Community Nodes Check

<!-- triage:2026-04-21 — extracted from claudeclaw-features n8n-templates priority 9 -->

- [PATTERN] **Анимация из рисунков**: scheduleTrigger/webhook → загрузка рисунков → image-to-video API (Runway/Kling/Hailuo) → сборка анимации → публикация или уведомление. Использовать для персонализированного детского контента AiGeneration. Риски: нестабильность внешних API + высокая сложность настройки (complexity: high). Интеграция: добавить как отдельный n8n workflow с polling-паттерном (аналог async kie.ai шаблона). <!-- decay:2026-04-06 tier:cold rel:0.58 -->

- **GOTCHA: n8n template import via MCP API fails silently if required community nodes are missing** — templates using `firecrawl`, `apify`, or other community nodes import without error but nodes are broken. Fix: check installed community nodes BEFORE importing templates. If missing → install via UI first, or import manually through the n8n UI (Settings → Community Nodes → Install). <!-- decay:2026-04-06 tier:cold rel:0.58 -->

### Health Check Sequence (Cross-Project)

- **PATTERN: Health check run order** — (1) n8n workflows status (active/inactive), (2) site HTTP check across all language variants, (3) analyze errors in execution logs, (4) prioritize tasks by impact. Run in this sequence to catch cascade failures before diving into code. <!-- decay:2026-04-06 tier:cold rel:0.58 -->

## Distilled 2026-04-20

### n8n Workflow Fixes

- **FIX: duplicate ingestion from two pipelines** — ingest-bot wrote `_incoming.jsonl` (triggering cron-sync) AND called n8n webhook simultaneously, causing double-pushes to vault. Fix: disable cron, use n8n as primary pipeline only.
- **FIX: n8n + cron race condition on git push** — both n8n and a cron job were pushing to git, causing conflicts. Fix: comment out cron entry with inline reason for easy rollback.
- **FIX: `fetch is not defined` in n8n Code node** — `ReferenceError: fetch is not defined` in task runner sandbox. Only `HTTP Request` nodes have network access; `fetch()`, `$http`, `?.`, `?:` are unavailable. Fix: replace Code node fetch calls with HTTP Request nodes.
- **FIX: Alert Engine sends 'undefined' via Telegram** — `={{ $json.message }}` without checking if `message` is defined. Fix: add IF node or filter before Telegram node to guard against undefined.
- **FIX: n8n workflow stays active after `active=f` SQL update** — n8n scheduler holds state in in-process cache. Full deactivation sequence: (1) SQL `UPDATE workflows SET active=false`, (2) n8n CLI `update:workflow --id=X --active=false`, (3) n8n service restart.
- **FIX: GDELT API 429 / IP block** — `1 request per 5 seconds` rate limit; with repeated violations, IP gets banned. External resolution required. Pattern: insert Wait nodes between GDELT requests, reduce frequency.
- **FIX: `varchar(10)` too short for `current_bias` column** — Seasonality Engine failed on longer bias strings. Fix: `ALTER TABLE seasonality_data ALTER COLUMN current_bias TYPE varchar(20)`.
- **PATTERN: n8n rate limit mitigation** — when workflows hit HTTP 429, insert Wait nodes between requests or reduce trigger frequency. If IP-banned: requires external (CDN/proxy) resolution.

## Distilled 2026-04-19

### YouTube Pipeline Fix

- **FIX: Missing `_incoming.jsonl` entry for YouTube video** — n8n pipeline did not create `_incoming.jsonl` for a processed video (GBbbXlfHkS8). Root cause unclear from transcript. Fix: manual intervention. Preventive: add explicit validation step in pipeline that checks `_incoming.jsonl` write succeeded before marking video as processed.

### Automated Vault Routing Pattern

- **PATTERN: `video-insight-router.js` pipeline** — classifies insights from YouTube notes, writes to `30-Resources/…` destinations based on routing-map.md, marks `routed: true` after successful vault pull. Auto-pull every ~15 minutes keeps vault in sync.

## Triage 2026-04-22

- [PATTERN] **n8n backup to Google Drive**: Scheduled trigger → n8n API (GET /workflows) → Google Drive upload node. Requires: Google Drive OAuth2 (use existing `0a4JFSW3JyCsi8wo` credential), target folder ID. Риски: ошибка OAuth2 блокирует весь бэкап; скрипт очистки может удалить актуальные данные. Рекомендация: версионировать имена файлов по дате, не перезаписывать.
- [PATTERN] **Автоматизация нарезки видео для соцсетей (RenderIO + OpenAI)**: scheduleTrigger/webhook → OpenAI (script/scene breakdown) → n8n-nodes-renderio (видеонарезка) → Google Drive upload → уведомление. Установить community node `n8n-nodes-renderio`. Риски: зависимость от внешних API + OAuth2 для Google Drive/Sheets.

## Distilled 2026-03-30

### n8n IF Node Unary Operators

- **IF nodes with unary operators require `singleValue: true`** — without this flag, unary operators (e.g. `exists`, `notExists`) silently misroute. Always set `singleValue: true` when using unary condition operators in IF nodes. <!-- decay:2026-03-30 tier:cold rel:0.475 -->

## Distilled 2026-03-29

### API Fallback Pattern

- **When browser-based UI is blocked: pivot to direct API calls** — if browser upload/interaction is blocked by security restrictions, switch to the service's native API endpoint directly (e.g., File Upload → Image Generation → Download flow). Applicable to Kling, Midjourney, and similar SaaS platforms with both UI and API access. <!-- decay:2026-03-29 tier:cold rel:0.46 -->

## Distilled 2026-03-25

### Audio API & Media Format Handling

- **FormData over manual multipart**: Whisper API returns 400 (Invalid file format) when multipart/form-data boundary is constructed manually — use native `FormData` API instead. Manual boundary construction is error-prone. <!-- decay:2026-03-25 tier:cold rel:0.4 -->
- **Pre-convert audio to mp3 before Whisper**: validate and convert audio format with ffmpeg to mp3 before Whisper API call — avoids format-negotiation failures across .ogg, .m4a, and other container formats. <!-- decay:2026-03-25 tier:cold rel:0.4 -->

### Docker Volume & Filesystem Paths

- **Always use host-mapped paths for `fs` operations**: when a service runs in Docker with a volume mount, `fs.existsSync()` / `fs.readFile()` must use the host-side mount path (e.g. `/opt/n8n/telegram-bot-api-data`), NOT the container-internal path (e.g. `/var/lib/telegram-bot-api`). Verify volume mappings before any direct filesystem access. <!-- decay:2026-03-25 tier:cold rel:0.4 -->

### Stateful Claude Sessions in n8n

- **One session per user, persist and resume**: for Claude Code / Claude API stateful conversations via Telegram or webhook, create one `--session-id` UUID per `chatId` and store it in handler state. Pass `--resume <session-id>` on all subsequent messages from that user to maintain conversation context across interactions. <!-- decay:2026-03-25 tier:cold rel:0.4 -->

