## Distilled 2026-03-24

### n8n Expression Engine Limitations

- **IF node output indices unreliable**: n8n expression engine cannot evaluate ternary operators (`? :`) or optional chaining (`?.`) correctly — outputs always route to FALSE branch. **Fix**: remove IF node; use HTTP Request node's native `continueOnFail` + `onError` error handling instead. <!-- decay:2026-03-24 tier:cold rel:0.385 -->
- **Avoid conditional branching (IF/Switch)** when downstream node error handling suffices — use node-native error controls (`continueOnFail`, `onError`) to reduce expression evaluation surface area. <!-- decay:2026-03-24 tier:cold rel:0.385 -->

### External API Calls

- **Use HTTP Request MCP tool** for all external network calls inside n8n — the task runner sandbox does not expose `fetch` or `axios`. <!-- decay:2026-03-24 tier:cold rel:0.385 -->
- **Validate model IDs** against a working reference node before using in new Claude call nodes. Last verified working ID: `claude-sonnet-4-5` (confirmed 2026-03-22; `claude-sonnet-4-6-20250514` returns 404). <!-- decay:2026-03-24 tier:cold rel:0.385 -->
- **Add guard clauses** before accessing `response.content[0].text` in downstream processing nodes — failed API calls return error objects, not structured responses. Pattern: return `{skipped: true}` when extraction errors. <!-- decay:2026-03-24 tier:cold rel:0.385 -->

### Workflow Reliability

- **Commit workflow changes immediately** after a fix is confirmed working — preserves tested state and enables clean rollback. <!-- decay:2026-03-24 tier:cold rel:0.385 -->
- **Case-insensitive project lookup + explicit mapping**: when batch processing stalls on name resolution, print the project→key mapping at startup and verify CLI args match storage keys exactly (case and spacing). <!-- decay:2026-03-24 tier:cold rel:0.385 -->

### AI Agent Patterns

- **Hybrid routing — Haiku→Sonnet two-stage**: use Haiku for fast/cheap classification, Sonnet for deep analysis. Reduces costs while maintaining accuracy on complex decisions. <!-- decay:2026-03-24 tier:cold rel:0.385 -->
- **Content-first analysis**: pass full text content to analyzer nodes (not just metadata/statistics) — semantic pattern detection requires actual content, not surface counts. <!-- decay:2026-03-24 tier:cold rel:0.385 -->
- **State-driven deduplication**: track processed insight hashes + timestamps in a state file to prevent duplicate task generation across multiple router runs. <!-- decay:2026-03-24 tier:cold rel:0.385 -->
- **Sub-agent delegation via MCP**: connect n8n to Claude Code via MCP to delegate workflow creation/debugging tasks. Claude Code with n8n Skills knowledge base can plan workflow logic before implementing, reducing errors vs direct generation. <!-- decay:2026-03-24 tier:cold rel:0.385 -->
- **English prompts for token efficiency**: Claude processes English prompts significantly cheaper than Russian/other languages — use English for all automated n8n prompt nodes. <!-- decay:2026-03-24 tier:cold rel:0.385 -->

### Notification Architecture

- **Tri-channel notification pattern**: critical findings → Telegram (real-time alert), medium-priority tasks → Obsidian note (persistent todo), low-priority flags → state file (background monitoring). <!-- decay:2026-03-24 tier:cold rel:0.385 -->

## Video Notes Distilled 2026-03-24

### Claude Code + n8n MCP Integration (from youtube-notes/n8n/)

- **Plan Mode before implementation**: always activate Planning Mode in Claude Code before workflow creation. Claude first builds a logical dependency map, then implements — significantly fewer structural errors than direct generation without planning. <!-- decay:2026-03-24 tier:cold rel:0.385 -->
- **n8n API key setup for MCP**: create API key at Settings → n8n API → Create API Key; name it `mcp-n8n`. Add to `mcp.json` with instance URL (no trailing slash). Verify connection by asking Claude to list existing workflows. <!-- decay:2026-03-24 tier:cold rel:0.385 -->
- **Specialized Claude agent > generic**: Claude Code loaded with the n8n Skills GitHub knowledge base produces workflows with correct node architecture; generic Claude/ChatGPT generates workflows without logical pre-planning and produces more structural errors. <!-- decay:2026-03-24 tier:cold rel:0.385 -->
- **Enable auto-execute in Claude Code**: activate the "allow automatic execution without confirmation" setting. Without it, every operation requires manual approval, slowing workflow creation significantly. <!-- decay:2026-03-24 tier:cold rel:0.385 -->
- **mcp.json config pattern**: <!-- decay:2026-03-24 tier:cold rel:0.385 -->
  ```json
  { "n8n-api-key": "<key>", "url": "https://your-n8n-instance" }
  ```

### Claude Code Skills Management (from youtube-notes/ai-tools/)

- **Lazy Loading for skills**: store only the Description (when/why to invoke) in `CLAUDE.md`; keep full skill logic in individual `skill.md` files inside each skill folder. Load-on-demand reduces session context by ~50% (394 → 207 lines). <!-- decay:2026-03-24 tier:cold rel:0.385 -->
- **Remove duplicate skills**: audit installed skills for functional overlap; remove redundant ones. 22 skills → 15 after dedup — same functionality, lower context overhead. <!-- decay:2026-03-24 tier:cold rel:0.385 -->
- **Reference file for brand voice**: create `reference.md` with brand voice, content examples, audience description, and writing rules. Link content skills (SEO, copywriting, social) to this file for personalized output instead of generic results. <!-- decay:2026-03-24 tier:cold rel:0.385 -->
- **Skill Description must be explicit**: description must state clearly *when and why* Claude should invoke the skill instead of solving directly. Vague descriptions cause Claude to skip the skill entirely. <!-- decay:2026-03-24 tier:cold rel:0.385 -->
- **Use official Anthropic Skill Creator**: includes automated tests, before/after performance comparison, and trigger optimization — superior to community templates. <!-- decay:2026-03-24 tier:cold rel:0.385 -->
- **Don't pre-install skills speculatively**: install skills only when a specific task arises that Claude cannot handle natively. Target 12–15 active skills maximum. <!-- decay:2026-03-24 tier:cold rel:0.385 -->

### Token Optimization Patterns (from youtube-notes/ai-tools/)

- **English prompts in n8n nodes**: Russian-language prompts consume significantly more tokens than English equivalents — use English for all automated Claude call nodes in n8n workflows. <!-- decay:2026-03-24 tier:cold rel:0.385 -->
- **Sub-agent delegation for routine tasks**: delegate repetitive operations (video transcription, subtitle generation, content optimization) to cheaper sub-agents via n8n MCP rather than loading the primary Claude Code agent. <!-- decay:2026-03-24 tier:cold rel:0.385 -->
- **Obsidian as filtered memory backend**: structured Obsidian vault with tags and graph links allows Claude to read only 10–50 relevant notes instead of 1000+ — token savings up to 95% vs. flat file folder. <!-- decay:2026-03-24 tier:cold rel:0.385 -->
- **Caching as interim measure**: prompt caching reduces token costs ~10x but is a workaround; proper knowledge structure (Obsidian graph) achieves 95% savings structurally. <!-- decay:2026-03-24 tier:cold rel:0.385 -->

### Claude Code + Telegram Deployment (from youtube-notes/ai-tools/)

- **VPS requirements for Claude Code**: Ubuntu 22.04, minimum $4–6/month VPS (Vultr or equivalent). SSH access required for initial setup only; all subsequent interaction via Telegram. <!-- decay:2026-03-24 tier:cold rel:0.385 -->
- **Anthropic officially permits Telegram bridges**: WhatsApp, Telegram, Discord bridges are explicitly allowed per Anthropic ToS. Use `RebootPrompt.en` file (>1100 lines) to establish the bridge. <!-- decay:2026-03-24 tier:cold rel:0.385 -->
- **Upload large config files via VS Code Remote SSH** — do not paste into terminal. Files >100 lines are error-prone when copied inline. <!-- decay:2026-03-24 tier:cold rel:0.385 -->
- **Keep terminal access open for first 1–2 days**: Claude Code self-debugs by reading logs, but keep SSH available until system is stable. After stabilization, full Telegram-only operation is reliable. <!-- decay:2026-03-24 tier:cold rel:0.385 -->
- **Command approval mode**: keep enabled during initial deployment (first 1–2 days). Disable only after confirming stable operation. Acts as safety layer for server-side actions. <!-- decay:2026-03-24 tier:cold rel:0.385 -->
- **Four-level memory architecture**: configure Claude Code with hierarchical memory (session, project, user, global levels) for persistent context across Telegram conversations. <!-- decay:2026-03-24 tier:cold rel:0.385 -->

