- WordPress integration: use WP REST API posts endpoint with custom post type "reviews" or standard post with category <!-- decay:2026-03-24 tier:cold rel:0.385 -->
- Sentiment gate: only auto-publish if sentiment score > threshold (e.g., 0.8) — prevents negative review leakage <!-- decay:2026-03-24 tier:cold rel:0.385 -->
- Source: feature-watcher #77729 (8/10) <!-- decay:2026-03-24 tier:cold rel:0.385 -->

### PATTERN: YouTube видео → мультиплатформенный контент (8/10)

- Pipeline: YouTube URL input → transcript extract (YouTube Data API or Whisper) → AI reformat → publish as blog post (WordPress) + social captions (Instagram/TG) + newsletter <!-- decay:2026-03-24 tier:cold rel:0.385 -->
- Extends existing "Content repurposing pipeline" pattern — adds WordPress as output channel <!-- decay:2026-03-24 tier:cold rel:0.385 -->
- Rate limit: YouTube Data API has 10,000 units/day quota — batch processing should check quota before running <!-- decay:2026-03-24 tier:cold rel:0.385 -->
- Source: feature-watcher #77743 (8/10) <!-- decay:2026-03-24 tier:cold rel:0.385 -->

<!-- triage:2026-04-23 — extracted from claudeclaw-features n8n-templates priority 8-9 -->

### PATTERN: Автоматическое резервное копирование n8n в Google Drive (8/10)

- Scheduled trigger в n8n → экспорт всех workflows через n8n REST API → загрузка JSON-файлов в Google Drive папку <!-- decay:2026-03-24 tier:cold rel:0.385 -->
- OAuth2 Google Drive: один credential покрывает Drive API — создать dedicated service account, не личный аккаунт <!-- decay:2026-03-24 tier:cold rel:0.385 -->
- Риск: скрипт очистки старых бэкапов может случайно удалить актуальные данные — использовать retention policy по дате, не по количеству <!-- decay:2026-03-24 tier:cold rel:0.385 -->
- Integration: для VPS n8n (157.180.33.253) — бэкап через n8n API endpoint /api/v1/workflows, JWT auth <!-- decay:2026-03-24 tier:cold rel:0.385 -->
- Source: feature-watcher #77936 (8/10) <!-- decay:2026-03-24 tier:cold rel:0.385 -->

### PATTERN: Автоматизация нарезки видео для соцсетей через RenderIO + OpenAI (9/10)

- Pipeline: исходное видео (Google Drive) → OpenAI (транскрипция + выделение ключевых моментов) → RenderIO (нарезка по таймкодам) → Google Drive (готовые клипы) <!-- decay:2026-03-24 tier:cold rel:0.385 -->
- n8n-nodes-renderio: установить через npm в n8n instance (community node) — `npm install n8n-nodes-renderio` в container <!-- decay:2026-03-24 tier:cold rel:0.385 -->
- Google Sheets как job queue: входящие видео → обработанные → ошибки; OAuth2 credential покрывает Sheets + Drive <!-- decay:2026-03-24 tier:cold rel:0.385 -->
- Антипаттерн: не хранить API-ключи RenderIO в Set-нодах — только через n8n Credentials manager <!-- decay:2026-03-24 tier:cold rel:0.385 -->
- Применимость: YouTube Shorts, Instagram Reels, TikTok — один workflow, разные output-профили через Switch node <!-- decay:2026-03-24 tier:cold rel:0.385 -->
- Source: feature-watcher #77937 (9/10) <!-- decay:2026-03-24 tier:cold rel:0.385 -->

## Distilled 2026-04-22

### Infrastructure & Database Patterns

- **GOTCHA: pgvector extension missing from default `postgres:15` image** — `CREATE EXTENSION pgvector` fails silently or errors. Fix: replace image with `pgvector/pgvector:pg15`. Collation warning after pgvector install (Debian version mismatch) is functionally harmless.
- **GOTCHA: All embeddings fail (0 rows inserted) → wrong Gemini model or missing outputDimensionality** — incorrect model name (e.g., `gemini-embedding-001`) or missing `outputDimensionality` parameter causes silent failures. Fix: verify model name and set `outputDimensionality=768`.
- **GOTCHA: Postgres tables owned by `postgres` user → app user lacks permissions** — after migration, `n8n_admin` cannot access tables owned by `postgres`. Fix: `GRANT SELECT, INSERT, UPDATE, DELETE ON ALL TABLES IN SCHEMA public TO n8n_admin`.
- **PATTERN: PostgreSQL LISTEN/NOTIFY event bus** — use `pg_notify` trigger on `INSERT` into an `events` table to broadcast new events; verify with a `LISTEN` smoke test before connecting consumers.
- **PATTERN: Verify DB schema changes immediately after migration** — run direct queries and test inserts after any `CREATE TABLE`, `ADD COLUMN`, or trigger creation. Catches permission and trigger failures early.
- **PATTERN: Verify embedding model name and output dimensionality** — when debugging embedding failures, explicitly log the model string and `outputDimensionality` parameter; incorrect values produce 0 rows with no error.

### Workflow Reliability

- **PATTERN: n8n dry runs before activation** — use manual dry runs with test events before activating workflows to catch configuration errors (wrong HTTP methods, expression syntax) without affecting production.
- **PATTERN: Pass all data annotations between nodes** — fields annotated in early nodes (e.g., `_report_age_days` in Annotate Age) must be explicitly forwarded to downstream nodes (Build Gemini Prompt). Data transforms can silently drop annotation fields.
- **PATTERN: Price verification step for real-time signal agents** — agents processing market prices must verify input price is within tolerance of current market price before generating signals, preventing signals based on stale or synthetic data.
- **PATTERN: API endpoint fallback on IP ban** — when an API bans the VPS IP (e.g., Binance weight overload), switch to an alternative API with compatible format (e.g., Bybit public API for crypto prices). Update parsing to match new response schema.
- **PATTERN: Group API records by entity before aggregate metrics** — when an API flattens records (e.g., CFTC returning individual items), group by entity (commodity) and sort by date before calculating rank or percentile metrics; otherwise calculations run on single-record windows.
- **PATTERN: Handle multiple source datasets for same domain** — some data sources (CFTC) split data across multiple endpoints by instrument class (commodities vs financial futures). WF11 requires dual-dataset fetch with schema normalization.

### Agent Signal Integrity

- **FIX: PositioningAgent generated signal from stale COT data** — report age annotation was lost between nodes; downstream agent used 2022 data as if current. Fix: persist `_report_age_days` through all transforms; add age guard before signal emission.
- **FIX: Telegram message showed empty `refs:` despite `knowledge_refs` populated** — `telegram_text` read `signal.knowledge_refs` (often `[]` from Gemini) instead of an `effective_refs` fallback. Fix: compute `effective_refs` variable from multiple sources before building `telegram_text`.


### Extracted from claudeclaw-features triage (2026-04-23)

- [PATTERN] **Автоматизация рекламных креативов (NanoBanana + OpenRouter)**: web-форма (сайт + логотип + фото продукта) → OpenRouter multi-model → NanoBanana image gen → Google Drive вывод. Ключи: Anthropic API + OpenRouter API + Google Drive OAuth2. Применимо для content-factory AiGeneration.
- [PATTERN] **Лидогенерация через Apify + Claude + Gmail**: Apify scraper (сбор бизнесов по нише/гео) → Claude генерирует персонализированное письмо → Gmail отправка. Google Sheets как хранилище лидов. `scheduleTrigger → Apify → Claude → Gmail`. Риск: конфиденциальность данных, нужен opt-out механизм.
- [PATTERN] **Контент-пакеты YouTube (OpenAI + Gmail)**: n8n workflow генерирует полный пакет (заголовок, описание, теги, thumbnail-prompt, сценарий) из темы/идеи → отправка пакета на email. Интеграция: OpenAI API + Gmail OAuth2.

## Distilled 2026-04-24

### n8n Workflow Fixes

- **FIX: signals_v2 UNION + ORDER BY produced empty response** — UNION + ORDER BY interaction caused column aliasing/ordering conflict across union branches. Fix: separate into two independent queries.
- **FIX: signals_v2 used wrong column name 'created_at' for events table** — events table uses 'ts' not 'created_at'. Fix: correct column name to 'ts'.
- **FIX: n8n API execute endpoint disabled → Confluence Engine workflow untriggerable** — API execute endpoint was disabled in n8n settings, preventing manual trigger of workflows. Fix: re-enable execute endpoint in n8n API settings.
- **FIX: Format Alert returned array instead of object in runOnceForEachItem mode** — Code node returned `[{json:...}]` instead of simple object. Fix: return plain object directly from Code node when `runOnceForEachItem` is active.
- **FIX: Spam on subsequent ticks due to re-logging existing decisions** — alerts sent for already-logged decisions on every tick. Fix: implement dedup via `INSERT ... WHERE NOT EXISTS + RETURNING`; place Format Alert after Log node so it only fires for new decisions.
- **FIX: MacroAgent received stale COT event payload without current FRED values** — event payload from 2 days prior lacked current market state; MacroAgent prompt contained only regime labels. Fix: add 'Fetch regime state' Postgres node to WF17; patch 'Build Gemini Prompt' to inject `CURRENT MARKET STATE`.
- **FIX: WF6 Parse FRED lost series_id → indicator="" for all rows** — node did not pair items with their source series. Fix: indexed pairing `items[i]` with `$('FRED Series List').all()[i]` to restore series_id.
- **FIX: Fetch FRED indicators emitted duplicate items** — caused inflated prompt token count. Fix: deduplication within Build Gemini Prompt Code node.

### n8n Patterns

- **PATTERN: Backfill script for historical data corrections** — when updating historical records in a DB, use a separate backfill script that directly fetches, recalculates, and overwrites records rather than relying on scheduled workflows with `ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING` logic.
- **PATTERN: Dual-dataset fetch for split CFTC data** — CFTC splits COT data across multiple endpoints by instrument class (physical commodities vs financial futures). WF11 requires dynamic URL selection and dual-schema parsing logic within the same workflow.
- **PATTERN: Simplify with Filter node over Check Existing + Dedupe** — when Code node `runOnceForAllItems` fails on empty input, replace `Check Existing` + `Dedupe` with a plain `Filter` node for immediate actionability. Defer complex deduplication to a later version.
- **PATTERN: n8n scheduler refresh via deactivate/activate cycle** — to refresh an n8n scheduler's in-memory cron after workflow schema changes, perform a full deactivate/activate cycle (not just save). May require explicit 'deploy' action if production-guard is active.
- **PATTERN: Defensive null/undefined checks in Code nodes** — add guard clauses for null/undefined inputs in Code nodes (e.g., `Format Alert`) to prevent crashes when upstream deduplication or filtering emits empty items.
- **PATTERN: Build Confluence Engine as separate workflow** — when new agent signals have different characteristics (frequency, asset class, agent types) from existing 'Signal Brain' workflows, build a dedicated 'Confluence Engine' workflow rather than modifying existing ones.

## Distilled 2026-04-25

### n8n Error Handling

- **PATTERN: Configure n8n native Error Workflow** — n8n failed executions are silent by default. Fix: configure a dedicated Error Workflow (Workflow Settings → Error Workflow) with a Telegram/email alert node to surface failures immediately.
- **FIX: Format Alert node crashed on `d.action.toUpperCase()` for undefined** — Postgres node emitted empty item despite dedup. Fix: add defensive null check: `const action = d.action ?? ''; action.toUpperCase()`.
- **FIX: MacroAgent prompt received only regime labels without FRED values** — `macro_indicators` table was empty; `regime_state` was populated but event was 2 days old. Fix: add 'Fetch regime state' Postgres node; patch 'Build Gemini Prompt' to inject `CURRENT MARKET STATE`.
- **FIX: WF6 Parse FRED lost `series_id` — `indicator=""` for all rows** — `$input.all()` did not merge upstream series list. Fix: indexed pairing `items[i] ↔ $('FRED Series List').all()[i]` to restore series_id.
- **FIX: Fetch FRED indicators emitted duplicate items** — 3 upstream sources × 8 indicators caused inflated prompt tokens. Fix: deduplication within Build Gemini Prompt Code node.

### n8n Data Flow Patterns (from global-patterns 2026-04-25)

- **PATTERN: Defensive null/undefined checks in Code nodes** — add guard clauses for undefined inputs (e.g., `d.action ?? ''`) to prevent crashes when upstream dedup or filtering emits empty items.
- **PATTERN: LLM agent prompts need current state + historical context** — inject both: historical event context AND current state data (e.g., latest market indicators) in the same prompt. Missing current state = stale reasoning.
- **PATTERN: Explicit index pairing for multi-upstream merges** — when merging data from multiple upstream n8n nodes, pair by index (`items[i] ↔ upstream.all()[i]`) or use unique identifiers. `$input.all()` does not merge upstream data automatically.

